description:
Create a React context for managing campaign state throughout the game.

## Requirements
- New CampaignContext to manage:
  - Active campaign state
  - Current mode (free-play vs campaign)
  - Campaign CRUD operations

## Context API
```typescript
interface CampaignContextType {
  campaign: CampaignState | null;
  isCampaignMode: boolean;

  // Actions
  startNewCampaign: (length: 3 | 5 | 8 | 13, config: GameConfig) => void;
  resumeCampaign: () => void;
  abandonCampaign: () => void;
  recordGameResult: (results: GameResult) => void;
  updateParticipantBalance: (id: string, delta: number) => void;
  purchaseWeaponForParticipant: (id: string, weapon: WeaponType) => void;
  recordKill: (killerId: string, victimId: string) => void;
  advanceToNextGame: () => void;
  completeCampaign: () => void;
}
```

## Integration points
- Wrap App in CampaignProvider (in main.tsx)
- WeaponShop uses campaign balance when in campaign mode
- GameContext checks campaign mode for phase transitions
- AI uses campaign participant data for decisions

## Files to create/modify
- src/context/CampaignContext.tsx (new file)
- src/main.tsx (add provider)
- src/types/game.ts (ensure all types exported)
